
<div class="post-date">2024 Aug 17</div><p>
Hey, everyone. I built a blog with Bastian Bechtold&rsquo;s <a href="https://github.com/bastibe/org-static-blog"><code>org-static-blog</code></a>. It was
<a href="https://duckduckgo.com/?q=super+easy+barely+an+inconvenience&amp;ia=web">super easy&#x2014;barely an inconvenience</a>&#x2014;to set it up to write posts in Emacs.
</p>

<p>
But before I start posting, I want to test <a href="https://sampsyo.github.io/emfed/">Emfed</a>, the facility I&rsquo;m going to try to use to allow comments via Mastodon.
</p>

<p>
Let me know in the comments how it goes for you posting comments!
</p>
